args: *huff...* *pant...*\nFinally made it over the mountain.\nNot long now till I'm back at Luccy's side.
Whoa there, lass.\nThat's as far as you go.
Just a few friendly fellas what\nfollowed you out here to relieve you\nof those little trinkets you got.
The very same, aye. Made by the old\ncraftsman what used to work for the\nroyal family, weren't they?
Wouldn't be right, you keepin' such\ntreasures all to yerself, now would it?\nLet's have 'em here, love.
No way. These represent my\nupcoming marriage to Luccy.
So you're to be wed, eh? That's right—you\nforest-dwellers trade earrings at the altar.
You're young to marry yet, lass.\nCool your heels and consider those\nbaubles a charitable donation. Or...
So you plan on taking them by force, then?
Well... I'm still not handing them over.\nThey're part of my special Valentine's plan\nto live happily ever after with Luccy!
You don't say? Thing is, it's awful hard to\nlive happily ever after...if you stop livin'!
Hyeh heh heh. Scared to die, girl?\nThen hand 'em over, and do it fast!
Better do as he says. What kinda idiot\nblathers on about weddings and holidays\nwith a blade to her throat?

Besides, you're puttin' yourself in the
poorhouse givin' valuables away to some
loverboy. Might as well toss 'em by the
roadside at that point!
You don't give presents because it turns\nyou a profit. You do it to show the love you\ncarry in your heart.
Get a load of this dunce, boys. Gah ha ha!\nThat hippity-hoppity head fulla Valentine's\nfluff is about to be lying in the dirt!
Getting to spend Valentine's Day with you\nand your mother makes it the happiest day\nof my life, year after year.
One day, when you're all grown up, you\ncan celebrate it by showering the person\nYOU love with presents, Chelsea.
Say again? You got rocks for brains, or—
Spending Valentine's with the one you love\nmakes it the happiest day of your life...
So I'm spending it with Luccy. This year,\nand the year after, and the year after that.
I'll give him so many presents, he'll be the\nhappiest boy in the whole wide world.
Which means these earrings are Luccy's\nhappiness. And anyone who gets in the\nway of Luccy's happiness...
I'll delete you all...\nDelete... Delete... DELETE!
That takes care of those nasty obstacles.\nI'll be home soon, Luccy. Wait for me...
Hm? Oh, sorry! Did I worry you? I know\ntoday's present is a bit later than usual.
That's not what I meant! You're bleeding!\nWhat in the world happened to you?
Oh, this? I was on my way over with your\ngift when some silly bandits held me up.
No need to worry, though!\nI didn't let them lay a finger on it.
The GIFT is fine? Chelsea, you're...!\nUgh, why do you always do this?!
Please take it, Luccy.\nThis is my way of saying—
Why would you risk your life over this?\nDid you really think that would make me\nhappy?!
But it's Valentine's Day, and I tried\nmy best to show you how I feel, so—
Did I ever ask you for presents?\nDid I say you had to try your best\nat ANYTHING for my sake?
Well, no, but I want you to be happy,\nso I'll do whatever it takes to make that—
If you're going to keep doing things like \nthis, I never want another present from\nyou! EVER!
You don't...want any more presents\nfrom me. Never, ever, ever, huh?
I understand, Luccy.\nI'll do as you ask.
I'll stop with the presents.\nSo, please...
Look, Chelsea. I'm sorry I yelled. But I'm\nbeing dead serious when I say I'd be much\nhappier if you'd stop with all the gifts.
Valentine's Day with the one I love...\nMy happy future... Gifts given with\nall my heart...
If he doesn't want any of that...
